<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="119">
6. 
<taxonomicName authority="Walker, 1869" authorityName="Walker" authorityYear="1869" class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Velarifictorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Velarifictorus (Velarifictorus) aspersus" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="aspersus" subGenus="Velarifictorus" subSpecies="aspersus">Velarifictorus (Velarifictorus) aspersus aspersus (Walker, 1869)</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="119" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="119">Remarks.-</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="119">
This species is one of the two species of the cosmopolitan genus 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Gryllidae" genus="Velarifictorus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Velarifictorus" order="Orthoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Velarifictorus</taxonomicName>
Randell, 1964 (
<taxonomicName lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" rank="tribe" tribe="Modicogryllini">Modicogryllini</taxonomicName>
) found in Kuala Belalong. Male genitalia resemble that of the species illustrated in 
<bibRefCitation author="Ingrisch, S" journalOrPublisher="Entomologica Scandinavica" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" pagination="315 - 359" title="The genera Velarifictorus, Modicogryllus and Mitius in Thailand (Ensifera: Gryllidae: Gryllinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1163/187631298X00122" volume="29" year="1998 a">Ingrisch (1998a)</bibRefCitation>
. This species is widespread in Southeast Asia, and can be found in Thailand, Singapore, and Peninsular Malaysia (
<bibRefCitation author="Ingrisch, S" journalOrPublisher="Entomologica Scandinavica" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" pagination="315 - 359" title="The genera Velarifictorus, Modicogryllus and Mitius in Thailand (Ensifera: Gryllidae: Gryllinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.1163/187631298X00122" volume="29" year="1998 a">Ingrisch 1998a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Tan, MK" journalOrPublisher="National University Singapore, Singapore" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" title="Orthoptera in the Bukit Timah and Central Catchment Nature Reserves (Part 2): Suborder Ensifera." year="2012">Tan 2012</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Tan, MK" journalOrPublisher="National University of Singapore, Singapore" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" title="Orthoptera of Fraser's Hill, Peninsular Malaysia." year="2014">Tan and Kamaruddin 2014</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Tan, MK" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" pagination="21 - 40" title="A contribution to the knowledge of Orthoptera diversity from Peninsular Malaysia: Bukit Larut, Perak." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4111.1.2" volume="4111" year="2016">2016</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Dawwrueng, P" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="119" pagination="301 - 324" title="Species checklist of Orthoptera (Insecta) from Sakaerat Environmental Research Station, Thailand (Southeast Asia)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4306.3.1" volume="4306" year="2017">Dawwrueng et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Refer to 
<bibRefCitation author="Tan, MK" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="1" pageNumber="120" pagination="374 - 384" title="First Velarifictorus (Orthoptera: Gryllidae, Gryllinae) cricket described from Borneo (Southeast Asia) and notes on a co-occurring congener." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4282.2.10" volume="4282" year="2017 c">Tan et al. (2017c)</bibRefCitation>
for more details on the calling songs and species distribution.
</paragraph>
